We say: "Adolescents try to find their own unique position in social life. They fear making decisions and many are confused by such problems as whether to follow the elder's will or to be true to oneself, whether to go with the flow or to be a revolutionary. They easily make decisions or sacrifice decisions on games and videos. Also, many select their groups by superficial identity. They often care about shape and colour and ignore the importance of ones' position." A five-part cartoon, "Rent, sometimes for the homeless" was adapted from a former novel published by Giet Tien Phat Publishers by playwright Dinh Van Lon (Doan Ngoc Son Publishing House, 2009). Teenagers can find the truth about the real life in the "Moon Over-Drive" cartoon series adapted from Khanh Duy's book series became a blockbuster afterwards thanks to its commercial success at the Big C supermarket chain (Youth Publishing House, 2000). Popular girls and boys book series unveiled the inner heart of adolescents. If you are interested, let DT3D collect them and bring them to you.
